</para><quote depth="1"><quotepara depth="1">what is the correct http header
for Cc:?
</quotepara></quote><para depth="0">
first of all Cc: is _NOT_ a HTTP header, it's an email header.

</para><quote depth="1"><quotepara depth="1">I've tried
"/nCC: ".$cc; (where $cc = and email address)
</quotepara></quote><para depth="0">   ^
   |
   here's an error...

</para><quote depth="1"><quotepara depth="1">when I receive the first mail for the recipient
it shows the Cc: information in the mail, but it 
never send s the second mail.

</quotepara><quotepara depth="1">what am I doing wrong?
</quotepara></quote><para depth="0">
just try the following:

</para><para depth="0">&lt;?
